# 📱 Mobile Sales Dashboard — Power BI

![Mobile Sales Dashboard](./dashboard-preview.png)

An interactive Power BI dashboard analysing mobile phone sales performance across Indian cities, brands, payment methods, and time periods — with dynamic slicers for real-time filtering.

---

## Key Metrics

| Metric | Value |
|---|---|
| Total Sales | 68M |
| Total Transactions | 2K |
| Total Quantity | 331 |
| Avg. Sales per Transaction | 41K |

---

## Visuals & Charts

| Visual | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Total Sales by City | Donut Chart | City-wise sales across 15+ Indian cities |
| Total Quantity by Month | Line Chart | Monthly volume trend |
| Customer Ratings | Bar Chart | Distribution of 1–5 star ratings |
| Transactions by Payment Method | Pie Chart | Credit Card, Debit Card, UPI, Cash split |
| Total Sales by Mobile Model | Bar Chart | Top models — iPhone SE, OnePlus, Galaxy S21 |
| Total Sales by Day Name | Area Chart | Day-of-week sales pattern |
| Brand Summary Table | Table | Xiaomi, Samsung, Vivo, OnePlus, Apple |
| Slicers | Filters | Mobile Model, Payment Method, Brand, Day Name |

---

## Key Insights

- **Delhi** leads city-wise sales at 26.87%
- **Apple** highest brand sales at 15.38M
- **iPhone SE** top model at 6.6M
- Payment methods evenly split across all 4 types
- **Monday** highest day-of-week sales at 12.0M

---

## Skills Demonstrated

- KPI cards with custom icons
- Dynamic slicers for interactive filtering
- Donut, pie, bar, area, and line charts
- Data table for brand-level summary
- Mobile-optimised layout design
